 Brenda Finn , 30 , says losing her hair at the age of 14 destroyed her confidence .
She was left suffering crippling anxiety and depression after bullying forced her to leave school .
But her family paid for her to have eyebrows tattooed on , she says she is able to face the world .
She is calling for medical tattooing to become available on the NHS as she says it could have saved her years of emotional pain .